{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_queenofspades_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608713/1958022701/0912.xml":{"full_text":"A-32\nTHE EVENING STAR, Washington, D. C.\nT Business\nWashington Gas Reports\nNet 18 Pet. Above 1957\nBy DONALD B. HADLEY\nBur Financial editor\nWashington Gas Light Co. had net income of $1,502,348\nin January, an increase of around 18 per cent from $1,282,362\nin January last year, the company reported today.\nThe month\u2019s operating revenues of $8,252,520 were up 14.2\nper cent from $7,231,294 a year earlier. Operating expenses of\n$5\u00a361,652 were 11 per cent\nabove $5,909,327 in January 1\nlast year. 1\nAs previously reported. Jan- 1\nUary sales rose to 63,138,951\ntherms from 56,949.966 a year i\nearlier. Meters on January 31 3\ntotaled 370.118, compared with c\n361,716 a year earlier.\nProperty, plant and equip-\nment aggregated $133,782,464\non January 31, an increase of\n$10,197,328 on January 31, 1957.\nCouples Need to Watch\nSize of Their Estate\nJoint ownership of property\nby a man and his wife may be 1\nagainst their best interests and i\nresult in unnecessarily large\ntaxes if the joint estate is.\nlarger than SIOO,OOO. L\nThis was the warning of J\nthree members of the Estate\nPlanning Workshop of George\ntown University Law School to\nlnembers of the Fiduciaries j\nBection of the District Bankers\nAssociation at the section\u2019s\nmid-winter meeting at Colum\nbia Country Club last night.\nThe panel agreed that for\nestates of SIOO,OOO and less.!,\nJoint tenancy with right of i\nsurvivorship is the most!\nadvantageous arrange ment,\nproviding there is love and\nunderstanding in the home.\nHowever, estates have away\nOs growing and a couple may\nnot realize the value of their 1\nhouse, other real estate, bank 1\naccounts, securities, savings and 1\nloan accounts and other in-!\nvestments may have risen to 1\nthe point that in case of death i j\nthe tax liability will be heavier\nthan necessary, they said.\nPanel members were Paul R. 1\nDean, dean of the Georgetown 1\nLaw Center: Edward J.\nSchmuck. vice president and\ngeneral counsel. Acacia Mutual\nLife Insurance Co., and Joseph\nL. Whyte, vice president and\ntrust officer, American Secur-\ntty St Trust Co.\nFNMA Offering Prices\nShow Market Easing 1\nOffering prices for $250 mil- 1\nlion of debentures by the Fed\neral National Mortgage Asso-\nciation today indicated the ex-\ntent to which the market is\nsoftened since a week ago when\ncoupon rates were fixed.\nFor SIOO million of 10-year-\nsecondary market operations j\ndebentures the rate was fixed\nat 3 v s per cent with the idea\nof offering them at par. The\nactual offering price today was\n100*i.\nFor $l5O million of 5-year\ndebentures, the rate was fixed\nat per cent The offering\nprice was lOO 3\nThese fractional premiums\n.1\nMUTUAL FUNDS\n\u25a0'N\u2019lQit Quotations'\nnew YORK, Frt. 17 WPi.-Hitaiaal Simla\ntin Stcaritics Dealers, lot.\nBIS Sikei SIS Asked 1\nStvdn Fund 1 44 151 list Ins ft 11.)] 1215\n\u2022Hilts Fund 5.71 0.11 Inti Ret Fd 170 3.571\nSa las Okn lIS 4.12 lie Ca Sa 7.97 0.71 1\nSa Mu Fans 7.22 7.00 lav Tr Oita 0.79 9.01\nSitae fl Tr 1.12 145 litel 27.05 20 20\nSta On Ma 4.11 4.70 left Cal FO 4.12 4.74\nSISFOS 400 510 \u25a0Jlkaitaa 11.1019.11\nSIN FOB 711 702 KEYSTONE:\nSiNStkFO 3.49 102 Cast 01 29.14 21.11 1\nSIUIOEI 932 11.1! Cast 02 22.49 24.93\nSi T 9 Ortk 29 17 22.20 Cast 01 15.1911.5!\nIlaa o*l Ma 9.72 19.57 Cast 14 1.99 912\n14 la Tr In 19.11 29 57 Cast K1 7.79 0.41\nNaitiiFO 14.42 15 51 Cast K 2 14011.21\nOr! St In 21.12 21.17 Cast 91 14.9115.10 i\nBallack FO 11.1112.90 Cast 92 1.41 11 20 1\nCllltFoaO 111 7.22 Cast 91 112211.11 1\nCat tea FO 11.9111.79 Cast 94 1.11 7.55\nCaaaOa F 01915 10 94 Fail Cat 1.1211.47\nCltlatCtk 1.49 715 Kalckeitkr 9.47 I N\nCafltal Yea 4.41 491 Ui-taTr 111111.14 1\nCea 9ln Tr 21.94 21 21 Lenta Veet 111 1.41 1\nCken FO 15.1111.11 Ufa lav 11.7215.19 1\nCelaalal F 0 1.11 914 Lid las F 0 511 9.59\nCult* lac FO 701 127 \u2018Lie Sf M 41