25a0oooooMoiiaiUMMolriiMi\nOo\u00bbn Dolly, 4 to# Open Doily, 4 to 4 Open Doily, 4 to# Open Dally, 4#\ni stores In the service,\u201d he wrote.\n\u201cIn the future, you will re\nceive a monthly statement ln\neluding your original sales\nchecks from Central Charge\nService.\u201d The new service will\nbe available at any of the 91\nPeoples Drug stores In this\ns area.\nLonger terms than 30 days\ncan be arranged for large pur\nchases, a footnote to the letter\n1 said.\nIn Its entire 53-year history.\nthe company never has offered\nI credit to the general public\nbefore. Only a few exceptions\nr to this rule have been made by\nindividual store managers in\n1 the past under unusual cir\ncumstances, as In the case of\n1 doctors.\nfor the Lester Martin Founda\ntion, a charitable Institution\nholding 11,000 shares. It was\nnot offered In the form of a\nresolution calling for a vote of\nstockholders.\nMr. Goldstein said the Metro-\nGoldwyn-Mayer Studios, oper\nating subsidiary of Loew\u2019s, lost\nabout $7 million last year. He\nsaid estimated losses this year\nwould run between $lO and sls\nmillion.\nMr. Goldstein said book value\nof Loew's, Inc., was $25.73 a\ni share.\n\"Let's liquidate this studio\nYOUR\njdeSk\nfew\nMONEY'S WORTH\nBY SYLVIA PORTER\n7 Chemise' Key to Economy\n\u201cHow many millions of wom\nen are going to walk out on\nEaster Sunday In a new che\nmise?\u201d asked my luncheon com\nj panlon suddenly and In all\n'seriousness.\n\u201cTo start answering, your\nquestion with a question, what\u2019s\nthe weather going to be across\nthe country between now and\nApril 6?\u201d I came back just as\nseriously.\nHe nodded his head thought\nfully. \u201cYes, the weather. What\na heat wave pushing tempera\ntures Into the 70s in March\ncould do for retail sales? I\nsure hope we get the break.\u201d\n\u201cBut if we don\u2019t? If those\nunreliable weather forecasts\nturn reliable and a cold wave\nsweeps the country instead\nduring the weeks before Easter?\nWhat happens to sales then?\u201d\nAnswer Due Soon\n\u201cMy mid-April we'll have the\nanswer,\u201d he said. \u201cI\u2019m not\nwhile there's still something left\nfor stockholders,\u201d he said.\nA spokesman said the com\npany was not considering liqui\ndating the studio.\ngoing to guess. I won\u2019t predict i\nwhat consumers will do.\u201d ji\nFor an hour my companion: 1\n\u2014a highly informed Washing-M\nton economist\u2014and I had been\npulling apart the statistics on\nbusiness, had been trying toil\nreach a tentative conclusion on I\nthe outlook for a spring up- 1\nswing. 1\nJust before he asked me about\nthe chemise, he had been argu-;\nmg that the administration\nhad done enough for now to\ncushion the recession and addi-\ntional anti-slump moves should\nbe kept on the shelf until we\ncan see whether the decline Is\naccelerating or winding up.\nHla question underlines a\ncritical clue\u2014the strength of\nEgster retail sales. And his\ncomment about mid-April pin\npoints the date by which we\neither will have passed or\nmuffed the big test.\nSo far, you have been main\ntaining your buying fairly well. 1\nRetail sales are down about 2\nper cent from the peak, which\nisn\u2019t too bad considering the\nslide in incomes, in employ\nment. in profits. Sales of food\nand drugs actually are well I\nahead of last year and clothing\nIs holding Its own. Only the\nbig lines of autos and appli\nances have been hit hard:\nwhat\u2019s going on In those vital\nindustries is no secret.\nEarly Easter\nNow lt is five weeks before\nEaster. It\u2019s an early Easter\nthis year, and this factor by\nitself raises a key question\nabout weather\u2019s Impact on\nsales. The big selling season\ncomes after a recession winter,\nand this raises a key question\nabout consumer psychology.\nThe test is comming at a\ntime when consumers are tend\ning to down-grade their pur\nchases buy middle-lower\npriced lines instead of the top\npriced stuff\u2014and this raises a\nkey question about how retail\ners are meeting the challenge.\nYet, we have money to spend.\nThe retail sales figures In the\nface of the drop in incomes\nshows we're willing to spend in\ncomes and savings to buy goods.\nWe aren\u2019t scared. Even frrn\nareas of distress there are no\nreports of panic and in such\ncities as New York\u2014not Influ\nenced much by manufacturing\ndownturns\u2014sales are being\nmaintained.\nEaster and mid-April will\ntest the economv\u2019s power.\n(Distributed 195 S be The H\u00bb!l Stb6l\nInc All Rlfhu R\u00ab*\u00bberv*d>\nMartin Recalls 300\nBALTIMORE. Feb. 27 \u00abFI\nMartin Co. recalled 300 workers,\nmostly skilled toolmakers, who\nhave been out of work several\nmonths It Is believed the com\npany is stepping up missile\nproduction.","height":"28835","width":"18314"}}
